---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Laura | AIlchemy"
  description="Who Laura is, why she builds, and her perspective on working with AI."
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <div class="about-header">
      <div class="about-header-inner">
        <div class="about-tag">About</div>
        <h1>Built by Laura.</h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-body">
      <div class="about-content">
        <p class="lead">
          I'm a Scottish founder and strategist. I build AI-powered tools for financial services
          and help organisations understand what they're actually solving for before they build
          anything.
        </p>

        <p>
          For the last couple of years, I've been deep in the AI world — not as a spectator, but
          as someone who builds with it every day. The learning curve has been steep and sometimes
          absurd. AIlchemy is where I share what I've figured out.
        </p>

        <p>
          The name is a wordplay on AI + Alchemy. Turning curiosity into capability. Turning
          complex problems into working solutions. Turning raw AI into practical tools that do
          something useful for real people.
        </p>

        <h2>Why AIlchemy?</h2>

        <p>
          I noticed that a lot of the conversation around AI sits at two extremes: breathless hype
          or technical gatekeeping. Neither is useful if you're trying to actually build something.
        </p>

        <p>
          AIlchemy is the middle ground. Practical, honest, and generous with the detail. If I've
          figured something out, I share it. Not because I have all the answers, but because
          sharing is how we all get better faster.
        </p>

        <h2>What I build</h2>

        <p>
          Alongside AIlchemy, I'm building two standalone products: <strong>Bothy</strong>, which
          gives plain-language guidance to adults navigating complex financial forms, and
          <strong>The Atlas</strong>, which turns scattered evidence into a usable map so people
          stop building solutions to problems they can't see.
        </p>

        <p>
          Both came from real problems I encountered. Both use AI in ways that feel genuinely
          useful rather than novelty for novelty's sake.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          The best way to stay connected is through the mailing list below. Or find me on LinkedIn.
        </p>

        <EmailSignup
          heading="Stay in the loop."
          subtext="New guides, prompts, and tools — when they're ready, not on a schedule."
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-top: 5rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    background: var(--deep);
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
  }

  .about-header-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-tag {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--pink-light);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
  }

  .about-body {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 3rem 5rem;
  }

  .about-content .lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--deep);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.8rem;
  }

  .about-content strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-header {
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .about-body {
      padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
